<div id="top-content">
  <div class="heading-with-actions top-heading">
    <h1>
      <span translate="no">epp_dodger</span> 
      <small class="app-vsn" translate="no">(syntax_tools v4.0.3)</small>

    </h1>




      <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/syntax_tools/src/epp_dodger.erl#L66" title="View Source" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow">
        <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        <span class="sr-only">View Source</span>
      </a>

  </div>


    <section id="moduledoc">
<p>Bypassing the Erlang preprocessor.</p><p>This module tokenizes and parses most Erlang source code without expanding
preprocessor directives and macro applications, as long as these are
syntactically &quot;well-behaved&quot;. Because the normal parse trees of the <code class="inline">erl_parse</code>
module cannot represent these things (normally, they are expanded by the Erlang
preprocessor <a href="../../../../lib/stdlib/doc/html/epp.html"><code class="inline">//stdlib/epp</code></a> before the parser sees them), an extended
syntax tree is created, using the <a href="erl_syntax.html"><code class="inline">erl_syntax</code></a> module.</p>
    </section>

</div>

