            <pre translate="no">Options = [<a href="#t:option/0">option</a>()]</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Result = {ok, <a href="erl_syntax.html#t:forms/0">erl_syntax:forms</a>(), <a href="../../../../lib/stdlib/doc/html/erl_anno.html#t:location/0">erl_anno:location</a>()} |
          {eof, <a href="../../../../lib/stdlib/doc/html/erl_anno.html#t:location/0">erl_anno:location</a>()} |
          {error, <a href="#t:errorinfo/0">errorinfo</a>(), <a href="../../../../lib/stdlib/doc/html/erl_anno.html#t:location/0">erl_anno:location</a>()}</pre>

        </div>


<p>Similar to <a href="#parse_form/3"><code class="inline">parse_form/3</code></a>, but does a more quick-and-dirty processing of the
code. See <a href="#quick_parse_file/2"><code class="inline">quick_parse_file/2</code></a> for details.</p><p><em>See also: </em><a href="#parse/3"><code class="inline">parse/3</code></a>, <a href="#parse_form/3"><code class="inline">parse_form/3</code></a>, <a href="#quick_parse_form/2"><code class="inline">quick_parse_form/2</code></a>.</p>
